WEBVTT

00:02.243 --> 00:03.493
<i>- Inside
an impenetrable fortress.</i>

00:03.578 --> 00:04.745
<i>- Never in my life would I think</i>

00:04.838 --> 00:06.663
that anybody would be able
to get out of there.

00:06.748 --> 00:09.174
<i>- Two men's impossible dreams.</i>

00:09.259 --> 00:11.418
<i>- You cannot tunnel
out of Dannemora</i>

00:11.511 --> 00:12.669
unless you have a jackhammer.

00:12.754 --> 00:15.431
<i>- Meet two unlikely
partners in crime.</i>

00:15.590 --> 00:18.341
- It was impossible for her
to stop once she started.

00:18.426 --> 00:21.270
<i>- Together, they attempt
the unthinkable.</i>

00:21.354 --> 00:22.354
- Crazy.

00:22.513 --> 00:25.849
- Escape Dannemora.

00:25.933 --> 00:28.861
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:29.020 --> 00:30.279
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:30.438 --> 00:33.106
Some of the greatest stories
ever told

00:33.199 --> 00:35.367
start behind the bars.

00:35.526 --> 00:36.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:37.028 --> 00:40.706
<i>Locked up in the most
notorious prisons in the world,</i>

00:40.865 --> 00:45.210
<i>spied on by guards
and fellow prisoners.</i>

00:45.369 --> 00:48.872
<i>It takes a devious mind
to find a way out.</i>

00:48.956 --> 00:50.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.792 --> 00:53.210
<i>It could lead you to freedom,</i>

00:53.303 --> 00:55.879
<i>or it could cost you your life.</i>

00:55.963 --> 00:57.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:57.465 --> 01:01.635
But wouldn't you try when
you have nothing left to lose?

01:01.719 --> 01:08.558
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:08.643 --> 01:11.737
<i>[tense music]</i>

01:11.896 --> 01:15.398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:15.483 --> 01:18.401
When you're locked up in
Clinton Correctional Facility

01:18.486 --> 01:22.823
in upstate New York,
this is your world.

01:22.907 --> 01:28.745
A dark, dank cockroach-infested
8x6 cell.

01:28.838 --> 01:32.091
This place used to be
an insane asylum.

01:32.250 --> 01:34.751
Sometimes...

01:34.844 --> 01:37.930
sometimes it feels
like it still is.

01:38.089 --> 01:40.173
Between the screams
of your fellow inmates

01:40.266 --> 01:44.177
and the rock-hard cot,

01:44.262 --> 01:46.930
it's hard to sleep at night.

01:47.023 --> 01:48.849
But you better get used to it

01:48.942 --> 01:51.860
because if you're sentenced
to life here,

01:51.945 --> 01:54.613
the only way out
is in a body bag.

01:54.772 --> 01:57.023
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:57.117 --> 02:00.869
<i>The prison's imposing
30-foot-high, 7-foot-thick</i>

02:00.954 --> 02:04.790
<i>concrete perimeter wall looms
over the main thoroughfare</i>

02:04.874 --> 02:08.460
<i>of the tiny village
of Dannemora.</i>

02:08.619 --> 02:11.788
<i>It's a constant reminder
to its citizens</i>

02:11.881 --> 02:14.624
<i>of the evil
that lurks behind it.</i>

02:14.709 --> 02:17.219
- The very first thing that
you're really struck with

02:17.303 --> 02:23.884
is that massive perimeter wall
around this very old prison.

02:23.968 --> 02:26.136
<i>It looks ominous
and there's this feeling</i>

02:26.229 --> 02:27.554
<i>that there's
a lot of history here.</i>

02:27.647 --> 02:30.307
<i>A lot of dark history here.</i>

02:30.391 --> 02:33.068
- There's a shadow that
overcomes you and it's like,

02:33.227 --> 02:34.477
it gives you a chill

02:34.562 --> 02:35.571
and it just reminds you

02:35.730 --> 02:37.656
of like a castle.

02:37.815 --> 02:40.242
<i>Never in my life would I think</i>

02:40.326 --> 02:42.661
<i>that anybody would be able
to get out of there.</i>

02:42.820 --> 02:45.831
<i>Never.</i>

02:45.990 --> 02:49.326
<i>- When you look at Dannemora,
it's not flat,</i>

02:49.410 --> 02:53.005
and it's because
the wall has been poured

02:53.089 --> 02:55.507
directly onto the bedrock
of the mountain.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.427
<i>So you cannot tunnel
out of Dannemora</i>

02:58.586 --> 03:00.762
<i>unless you have a jackhammer.</i>

03:00.847 --> 03:04.591
<i>The only way out is either
breaching those front doors</i>

03:04.684 --> 03:07.594
<i>or going over.</i>

03:07.687 --> 03:11.023
- Who would even try to escape
this impregnable fortress?

03:11.182 --> 03:13.016
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:13.100 --> 03:16.445
A remorseless killer
named Richard Matt.

03:16.604 --> 03:19.114
He's doing 25 years to life.

03:19.273 --> 03:21.700
They called him Hacksaw because

03:21.784 --> 03:25.454
that was how he dismembered
his victim's body.

03:25.538 --> 03:29.449
All of his appeals have failed,
so in Matt's mind,

03:29.542 --> 03:35.047
the only path to freedom
no matter the odds is escape.

03:35.206 --> 03:41.294
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:41.387 --> 03:44.640
<i>- Richard Matt is a career
criminal and ruthless killer.</i>

03:44.799 --> 03:48.885
In 1997, Matt kidnapped
76-year-old

03:48.978 --> 03:50.646
William Rickerson,
his former employer,

03:50.730 --> 03:52.648
<i>threw him
in the back of his vehicle,</i>

03:52.807 --> 03:54.224
<i>and proceeded to drive around</i>

03:54.308 --> 03:56.401
<i>for approximately
the next 27 hours,</i>

03:56.560 --> 03:58.812
<i>stopping repeatedly
to torture Rickerson</i>

03:58.905 --> 03:59.988
in an attempt to extort money.

04:00.147 --> 04:02.741
<i>When this failed,
out of frustration,</i>

04:02.900 --> 04:04.993
Matt simply broke
Mr. Rickerson's neck

04:05.078 --> 04:08.071
and using a hacksaw
dismembered his body,

04:08.155 --> 04:10.490
<i>disposing off it
in the Niagara River.</i>

04:10.574 --> 04:12.909
<i>- Matt fled to Mexico,</i>

04:13.002 --> 04:16.413
and he actually committed
a second murder.

04:16.497 --> 04:20.175
<i>Was incarcerated
by the Mexican authorities</i>

04:20.260 --> 04:22.836
<i>and then nine years later
he ended up</i>

04:22.929 --> 04:25.430
at Clinton Correctional
Facility to be doing his time.

04:25.589 --> 04:28.758
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:28.843 --> 04:33.430
- Richard Matt, he could sell
water to a drowning man.

04:33.514 --> 04:35.015
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:35.099 --> 04:37.025
<i>I mean, if you wanted anything
you could get it from him.</i>

04:37.184 --> 04:38.268
<i>He was a hustler.</i>

04:38.352 --> 04:39.436
<i>Richard Matt knew
how to manipulate</i>

04:39.520 --> 04:42.772
<i>and move through
that environment.</i>

04:42.865 --> 04:46.201
<i>- Richard "Hacksaw" Matt has
been trapped behind the walls</i>

04:46.286 --> 04:50.289
<i>of Dannemora
for the last seven years,</i>

04:50.448 --> 04:52.949
<i>and he desperately wants out.</i>

04:53.034 --> 04:55.201
<i>- My dad, Richard Matt,</i>

04:55.295 --> 04:56.870
<i>has mentioned escape</i>

04:56.963 --> 04:58.038
on numerous occasions,

04:58.122 --> 05:01.717
as if escape
is a for sure thing.

05:01.876 --> 05:03.793
<i>He spoke of Mexico often,</i>

05:03.878 --> 05:05.211
<i>that that's where
he wanted to be,</i>

05:05.296 --> 05:08.390
<i>painting on a beach somewhere.</i>

05:08.549 --> 05:12.802
- Richard Matt believes
that he can pull off an escape.

05:12.887 --> 05:14.229
Why?

05:14.314 --> 05:17.640
Because he's sure he can
manipulate the right people

05:17.725 --> 05:20.060
to get what he'll need.

05:20.144 --> 05:22.729
But how will he escape?

05:22.813 --> 05:25.574
His mind swirls
with the possibilities,

05:25.733 --> 05:27.650
thinking through each one.

05:27.735 --> 05:30.070
Searching for a fatal flaw.

05:30.154 --> 05:34.666
<i>Can he dismantle his cell door
and hide in a delivery truck?</i>

05:34.825 --> 05:37.827
<i>Or maybe build a ladder
to get over the wall?</i>

05:37.920 --> 05:40.997
<i>Can he threaten
or bribe the guards?</i>

05:41.090 --> 05:44.334
<i>Dig a tunnel?
Something? Anything?</i>

05:44.418 --> 05:47.512
<i>As long as it will get him
out of this hell hole.</i>

05:47.671 --> 05:51.183
This won't be Richard Matt's
first prison break.

05:51.342 --> 05:53.352
He once jumped the fence
at a county jail

05:53.511 --> 05:55.512
outside of Buffalo,

05:55.605 --> 05:59.682
but that was child's play
compared to Dannemora.

05:59.767 --> 06:01.276
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:01.435 --> 06:05.030
He needs help,
but who can he trust?

06:05.189 --> 06:06.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:06.774 --> 06:09.776
Only one man comes to mind.

06:09.860 --> 06:11.370
David Sweat.

06:11.529 --> 06:17.784
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:17.868 --> 06:19.461
<i>- David Sweat was incarcerated</i>

06:19.620 --> 06:20.870
<i>at Clinton Correctional Facility</i>

06:20.963 --> 06:22.872
as a result of his involvement

06:22.965 --> 06:26.876
<i>with the murder
of a Deputy Sheriff.</i>

06:26.969 --> 06:28.887
<i>- Sweat has been in Clinton
for 12 years,</i>

06:28.971 --> 06:33.049
<i>but he's been in and out of
prison most of his adult life.</i>

06:33.142 --> 06:34.801
<i>He's picked up
some valuable skills</i>

06:34.894 --> 06:36.395
<i>in prison woodworking shops</i>

06:36.479 --> 06:39.231
<i>and working as
an electrician's assistant.</i>

06:39.390 --> 06:42.234
<i>He also happens to be
Richard Matt's neighbor</i>

06:42.393 --> 06:43.893
<i>in the cell block.</i>

06:43.986 --> 06:45.061
<i>- Richard Matt and David Sweat</i>

06:45.154 --> 06:48.657
<i>really bonded
from doing art together.</i>

06:48.816 --> 06:51.067
<i>The friendship had started</i>

06:51.152 --> 06:54.162
<i>when David saw a painting
Richard Matt had done,</i>

06:54.247 --> 06:55.488
<i>and David really admired it.</i>

06:55.573 --> 06:56.832
<i>He thought it was great.</i>

06:56.991 --> 06:59.909
<i>And they started to really
paint together a lot,</i>

07:00.002 --> 07:02.921
<i>and that's when
they began planning,</i>

07:03.080 --> 07:08.168
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:08.252 --> 07:12.431
<i>- Sweat and Matt search for
any weakness in the prison,</i>

07:12.515 --> 07:15.925
<i>and they come up with a plan
that might just work.</i>

07:16.010 --> 07:18.019
<i>They will remove
their cell doors,</i>

07:18.104 --> 07:21.273
<i>sneak out of the cellblock
to the industry yard</i>

07:21.357 --> 07:24.767
<i>and climb over that portion
of the massive perimeter wall.</i>

07:24.852 --> 07:26.019
<i>- The reason why they were going</i>

07:26.112 --> 07:28.438
to do this particular plan
is that the inmates

07:28.531 --> 07:30.782
were fully aware
that there was no officer

07:30.941 --> 07:34.035
<i>stationed at that
particular wall tower.</i>

07:34.195 --> 07:36.446
<i>- The first step of their plan</i>

07:36.530 --> 07:39.291
<i>is to remove the lock
on the cell door.</i>

07:39.450 --> 07:42.627
<i>To do that, they need
a specialized security</i>

07:42.786 --> 07:45.630
<i>screwdriver bit,
known as a Torx,</i>

07:45.789 --> 07:48.875
<i>but they don't have access
to any tools.</i>

07:48.959 --> 07:53.630
<i>They must find someone who can
get them what they need.</i>

07:53.714 --> 07:58.643
<i>Richard Matt, always scheming,
knows just who to exploit.</i>

07:58.728 --> 08:02.305
<i>The civilian supervisor of the
tailor shop where he works,</i>

08:02.389 --> 08:03.648
Joyce Mitchell.

08:03.807 --> 08:09.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:09.480 --> 08:13.909
<i>Joyce has a weakness,
his buddy David Sweat.</i>

08:13.993 --> 08:16.578
- I think Joyce Mitchell
was bored

08:16.737 --> 08:20.999
and was tired of living
in this town

08:21.083 --> 08:24.836
<i>and in this marriage
for 20 years,</i>

08:24.921 --> 08:28.414
and I think
she found excitement.

08:28.499 --> 08:33.178
<i>I noticed many interactions
with Joyce and David Sweat.</i>

08:33.337 --> 08:36.673
They would go in the backroom
to count material.

08:36.766 --> 08:38.767
<i>- But Eric isn't the only one
who noticed</i>

08:38.926 --> 08:40.602
<i>that David Sweat
and Joyce Mitchell</i>

08:40.761 --> 08:42.512
<i>would disappear
from the workroom</i>

08:42.596 --> 08:44.764
<i>for extended stretches.</i>

08:44.848 --> 08:46.015
- Somebody wrote a note

08:46.100 --> 08:48.860
stating that he was
having sexual relations

08:49.019 --> 08:52.355
and disappearing into the back
material room with Joyce.

08:52.448 --> 08:54.282
<i>So with that, he was removed.</i>

08:54.367 --> 08:59.204
<i>That's when Richard Matt,
"Hacksaw," moved in.</i>

08:59.363 --> 09:02.198
<i>- Joyce knows Matt
is friends with Sweat</i>

09:02.291 --> 09:06.202
<i>and uses him to pass messages.</i>

09:06.295 --> 09:10.123
<i>Richard Matt
now sees his opening.</i>

09:10.216 --> 09:13.209
<i>He doesn't risk asking
for the Torx bit right away.</i>

09:13.294 --> 09:15.295
<i>He starts small.</i>

09:15.379 --> 09:18.223
<i>He asks Mitchell
for two pairs of glasses</i>

09:18.382 --> 09:20.559
<i>with LED lights built into them.</i>

09:20.718 --> 09:24.971
<i>He says they are so he
and Sweat can paint at night.</i>

09:25.064 --> 09:29.892
- Slowly but surely Matt asks
for more and more and more.

09:29.986 --> 09:32.320
<i>- But to ask her for a Torx bit,</i>

09:32.479 --> 09:35.815
<i>something that clearly has
nothing to do with painting,</i>

09:35.899 --> 09:37.734
<i>Matt needs to leverage,</i>

09:37.827 --> 09:40.245
<i>something he can
blackmail her with.</i>

09:40.404 --> 09:43.740
- The next thing he asked for
is some nudes.

09:43.824 --> 09:46.743
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

09:46.827 --> 09:52.749
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:52.833 --> 09:54.259
<i>And she does.</i>

09:54.343 --> 09:57.170
<i>She sends pictures of herself.</i>

09:57.263 --> 10:00.765
<i>- Matt now knows Mitchell
will get them the Torx bit,</i>

10:00.924 --> 10:02.684
<i>but they will need to figure out</i>

10:02.768 --> 10:06.346
<i>what size fits the screws
on the lock.</i>

10:06.430 --> 10:10.350
<i>This is where David Sweat's
shop skills come into play.</i>

10:10.434 --> 10:13.603
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:13.696 --> 10:16.531
<i>- He takes a little imprint
of the screw.</i>

10:16.616 --> 10:19.534
<i>He put some putty
on this Torx screw,</i>

10:19.693 --> 10:22.787
gets a mold of the screw,
get some ink

10:22.946 --> 10:26.532
and a piece of paper
and uses the mold as a stamp

10:26.617 --> 10:30.536
<i>to draw out or map out
the size of the screw.</i>

10:30.621 --> 10:32.964
<i>He hands that piece
of paper off to Matt</i>

10:33.123 --> 10:36.292
<i>who then hands it over
to Joyce Mitchell.</i>

10:36.385 --> 10:38.553
<i>- Joyce gets
the right-sized Torx bit</i>

10:38.712 --> 10:40.963
<i>and gives it to Richard Matt.</i>

10:41.048 --> 10:44.476
<i>Now he has to smuggle them
out of the tailor shop,</i>

10:44.635 --> 10:47.729
<i>which requires passing
through a metal detector</i>

10:47.888 --> 10:50.056
<i>on the way back
to the cell block.</i>

10:50.149 --> 10:54.569
<i>If he gets caught, the
consequences will be severe.</i>

10:54.654 --> 10:56.571
<i>- You walk through
that metal detector,</i>

10:56.656 --> 10:58.156
you feel like you're
in a spotlight

10:58.315 --> 11:00.659
and it's just shining on you
as you walk through.

11:00.818 --> 11:03.569
And it's one of the most
uncomfortable times

11:03.654 --> 11:05.321
<i>because you don't know
if you're gonna get picked off</i>

11:05.406 --> 11:06.748
<i>and thrown on the wall.</i>

11:06.832 --> 11:09.075
You know, people get beat up.

11:09.168 --> 11:11.077
People will disappear.

11:11.170 --> 11:13.171
<i>- But how will Richard Matt</i>

11:13.255 --> 11:16.833
<i>get the Torx bit through
the metal detector?</i>

11:16.926 --> 11:19.511
- If you have something
like a set of headphones

11:19.670 --> 11:21.763
<i>that you know
there's a hollow spot in,</i>

11:21.922 --> 11:24.933
<i>but they will also ring in the
metal in the metal detector,</i>

11:25.092 --> 11:26.685
<i>well, that's a good place</i>

11:26.844 --> 11:28.770
to put something
of metal and contraband.

11:28.929 --> 11:30.855
<i>- Matt hides the Torx bit</i>

11:31.014 --> 11:33.766
<i>in the hollow compartment
of his headphones.</i>

11:33.859 --> 11:36.269
<i>When he returns to his cell,</i>

11:36.362 --> 11:38.279
<i>he hands them over to Sweat,</i>

11:38.364 --> 11:41.941
<i>who sets to work trying to
dismantle the cell door lock.</i>

11:42.025 --> 11:44.619
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:44.704 --> 11:46.612
<i>- David quickly finds out
this isn't working.</i>

11:46.697 --> 11:49.866
He's trying to fiddle with it.
It's not happening.

11:49.959 --> 11:51.876
<i>He can't get the cell door off.</i>

11:52.035 --> 11:54.546
<i>- Richard Matt and David Sweat
have broken many rules</i>

11:54.630 --> 11:59.217
<i>to get to this moment,
but it's a dead-end.</i>

11:59.376 --> 12:03.045
<i>Without a better plan,
they'll both spend</i>

12:03.130 --> 12:06.224
<i>the rest of their lives
wasting away behind bars.</i>

12:06.383 --> 12:09.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:14.066 --> 12:17.143
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:17.236 --> 12:19.979
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:20.063 --> 12:22.490
<i>Two Dannemora prisoners
are meticulously</i>

12:22.575 --> 12:25.410
<i>and furiously attempting
to break out of their cells</i>

12:25.494 --> 12:29.989
<i>at one of the most dangerous
prisons in New York State.</i>

12:30.073 --> 12:33.576
<i>They've been at it for a month,
but there's a problem.</i>

12:33.660 --> 12:35.828
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:35.913 --> 12:37.747
<i>Richard Matt and David Sweat's</i>

12:37.831 --> 12:41.259
plan to escape the
Clinton Correctional Facility

12:41.418 --> 12:46.005
has been thwarted
by a handful of screws.

12:46.089 --> 12:49.517
No matter how hard they try,
they won't budge.

12:49.602 --> 12:53.262
They can't get to the locking
mechanism behind the plate.

12:53.347 --> 12:55.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:55.682 --> 12:57.850
Time to come up with plan B.

12:57.935 --> 12:59.769
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:59.853 --> 13:02.614
<i>- David is the one
that's thinking, okay,</i>

13:02.773 --> 13:04.941
how do I get from
point A to point B?

13:05.025 --> 13:06.951
How do I get out of this cell?

13:07.036 --> 13:10.288
<i>So David sees
that there's a vent</i>

13:10.447 --> 13:12.532
<i>at the back of his cell
behind his bed,</i>

13:12.625 --> 13:15.535
<i>and he knows that
if he cuts around that vent</i>

13:15.619 --> 13:17.796
<i>it leads to the catwalks.</i>

13:17.880 --> 13:20.206
- The area behind the cells
are what we call the catwalk.

13:20.290 --> 13:21.374
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:21.458 --> 13:24.460
<i>And everything
that services the cells,</i>

13:24.545 --> 13:27.547
<i>plumbing, electrical,
cable for the TVs,</i>

13:27.631 --> 13:31.142
<i>all of that is contained
in those catwalks.</i>

13:31.227 --> 13:34.145
- David Sweat was allowed
into the catwalk areas

13:34.304 --> 13:36.981
on a number of occasions
for electrical work

13:37.140 --> 13:40.309
<i>that he would do
on fellow inmate cells.</i>

13:40.394 --> 13:42.812
<i>- To access the catwalks,</i>

13:42.896 --> 13:44.814
<i>Sweat's going to need something</i>

13:44.907 --> 13:47.909
<i>to cut out the vent
behind his bed.</i>

13:47.993 --> 13:51.571
<i>David Sweat is a mastermind
at exploiting weaknesses</i>

13:51.655 --> 13:54.240
<i>in the physical structure
of the prison,</i>

13:54.333 --> 13:58.419
<i>but Richard Matt's genius,
