allowed these two to break out.

28:23.693 --> 28:28.872
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:29.031 --> 28:32.951
<i>- For the last 50 days,
Sweat has toiled away</i>

28:33.044 --> 28:35.295
<i>in the claustrophobic bowels
of the prison.</i>

28:35.380 --> 28:38.716
<i>Armed with the concrete
drill bits and a new punch,</i>

28:38.800 --> 28:40.551
<i>he finally has a way</i>

28:40.710 --> 28:43.962
<i>to breach the prison's
infamous perimeter wall.</i>

28:44.055 --> 28:47.558
<i>He's hopeful he will leave
this hell hole behind</i>

28:47.642 --> 28:50.719
<i>as he heads to the gang box
with the power tools.</i>

28:50.803 --> 28:53.805
<i>[tense music]</i>

28:53.898 --> 29:00.988
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:01.147 --> 29:05.075
<i>- Unfortunately, by the time
that the bits were delivered</i>

29:05.160 --> 29:07.152
the gang box is gone.

29:07.236 --> 29:10.405
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:10.498 --> 29:13.992
<i>They're back to square one.</i>

29:14.076 --> 29:16.578
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:16.671 --> 29:18.997
<i>- It's looking pretty hopeless,</i>

29:19.081 --> 29:23.001
<i>but all of a sudden
everything changes.</i>

29:23.085 --> 29:29.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:29.350 --> 29:32.260
All this time
they've been working away

29:32.345 --> 29:35.430
next to a steaming hot pipe,

29:35.515 --> 29:41.436
but today for the first time,
the pipe is cold.

29:41.521 --> 29:45.190
The prison heating system
is off for the summer.

29:45.274 --> 29:46.950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:47.035 --> 29:51.538
This could be their way through.

29:51.623 --> 29:53.949
<i>- Sweat would later tell
investigators this is it.</i>

29:54.042 --> 29:56.293
I knew now that I had a route.

29:56.377 --> 29:59.704
<i>- They knew that if they're
able to breach into that pipe</i>

29:59.789 --> 30:02.123
then they would simply
breach on the other side

30:02.208 --> 30:05.302
of the perimeter
wall to freedom.

30:05.461 --> 30:08.055
<i>- David goes back to using
his hacksaw</i>

30:08.139 --> 30:12.884
<i>and he devises a clever way
to make the difficult cut.</i>

30:12.969 --> 30:15.554
- They had also found
a Mountain Dew bottle.

30:15.638 --> 30:18.148
<i>They would fill the Mountain
Dew bottle full of water</i>

30:18.233 --> 30:22.060
<i>and use it as a lubricant
as they cut through the pipe</i>

30:22.144 --> 30:25.489
to save the blades
and to keep the metal cool

30:25.573 --> 30:30.151
so it would be easier
to cut through that pipe.

30:30.236 --> 30:34.331
<i>- Cutting ten inches a night,
David finishes the first hole.</i>

30:34.415 --> 30:37.167
<i>- So when David's cutting
into the steam pipe,</i>

30:37.252 --> 30:40.838
<i>he has to then crawl through
that hole and pop out</i>

30:40.922 --> 30:42.497
<i>another part of the steam pipe</i>

30:42.582 --> 30:44.341
<i>which means he has
to cut his way out</i>

30:44.425 --> 30:48.169
once he is inside the pipe

30:48.254 --> 30:50.088
<i>- But the pipe's cramped.</i>

30:50.181 --> 30:54.259
<i>Cutting it from the inside
is incredibly difficult.</i>

30:54.352 --> 30:57.095
<i>- Being in that steam pipe,
it's very narrow.</i>

30:57.188 --> 30:58.438
<i>It's not huge.</i>

30:58.523 --> 31:02.609
And so he is working
in extremely close quarters

31:02.694 --> 31:03.777
<i>- Night after night,</i>

31:03.862 --> 31:07.856
<i>David Sweat
toils away at the cuts.</i>

31:07.940 --> 31:11.526
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:11.611 --> 31:14.362
<i>David makes his last cut.</i>

31:14.447 --> 31:16.114
<i>For the first time
since he arrived</i>

31:16.198 --> 31:19.543
<i>at Clinton Correctional
Facility in 2003,</i>

31:19.627 --> 31:23.204
<i>he's about to venture
outside its perimeter wall.</i>

31:23.289 --> 31:25.790
- David gets out of
the steam pipe.

31:25.875 --> 31:28.051
He walks down a long tunnel

31:28.136 --> 31:31.722
<i>that he realizes is underneath</i>

31:31.881 --> 31:33.640
<i>the streets above of Dannemora.</i>

31:33.725 --> 31:35.550
<i>At different points
in the tunnel,</i>

31:35.635 --> 31:38.896
<i>he sees that there are
different manholes.</i>

31:38.980 --> 31:41.315
<i>- He located a manhole cover,</i>

31:41.474 --> 31:43.558
<i>and he was able to go up</i>

31:43.643 --> 31:46.478
the ladder from the sewer,
prop the lid open.

31:46.562 --> 31:48.480
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:48.564 --> 31:52.317
- He goes out of the manhole,
he looks around,

31:52.401 --> 31:55.070
and he says to himself,
"This is perfect."

31:55.154 --> 31:58.823
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:58.917 --> 32:02.085
<i>- David has made it outside
the prison walls.</i>

32:02.170 --> 32:05.589
<i>He has successfully completed
the escape route.</i>

32:05.748 --> 32:09.000
<i>He could leave right now
if he wanted to,</i>

32:09.085 --> 32:11.678
<i>but Richard Matt isn't with him.</i>

32:11.763 --> 32:16.424
- Friends is a very loosely
used word

32:16.509 --> 32:21.271
because in prison
friends really don't exist.

32:21.356 --> 32:24.191
I've seen people
get stabbed in the neck

32:24.275 --> 32:27.027
by somebody they call friends

32:27.111 --> 32:29.696
<i>- Will David betray
his fellow inmate</i>

32:29.855 --> 32:34.451
<i>and leave him to rot on
the inside while he goes free?</i>

32:39.958 --> 32:43.785
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:43.869 --> 32:47.122
<i>- After 109 nights
of backbreaking work,</i>

32:47.206 --> 32:49.791
David Sweat's made his way
to the intersection

32:49.884 --> 32:53.136
of Barker Street
and Bouck Street,

32:53.221 --> 32:59.300
130 yards outside the walls
of the Dannemora prison.

32:59.385 --> 33:03.563
He wants to run
and never look back,

33:03.648 --> 33:08.393
but his partner in this
daring escape, Richard Matt,

33:08.477 --> 33:12.063
is still locked in his cell.

33:12.156 --> 33:15.575
Clock is ticking.

33:15.660 --> 33:17.911
<i>- David could have escaped,</i>

33:17.996 --> 33:19.904
but he didn't wanna
leave Matt behind.

33:19.989 --> 33:22.574
They were in this together.

33:22.658 --> 33:26.086
<i>- Dave and Richard Matt
planned, plotted,</i>

33:26.170 --> 33:28.246
<i>and they kept their mouth shut.</i>

33:28.330 --> 33:30.757
<i>It was teamwork.
That doesn't happen a lot.</i>

33:30.916 --> 33:33.010
Doesn't happen a lot in prison.

33:33.169 --> 33:34.678
Not at all.

33:34.837 --> 33:37.172
<i>- But it's not just Richard Matt</i>

33:37.265 --> 33:38.840
<i>that David Sweat is missing.</i>

33:38.924 --> 33:41.176
<i>He's also without his
getaway driver,</i>

33:41.260 --> 33:43.178
<i>Joyce Mitchell.</i>

33:43.262 --> 33:45.105
<i>The only way to get her
to show up</i>

33:45.189 --> 33:48.358
<i>is to rush back to his cell
before the 5:30 count,</i>

33:48.517 --> 33:51.111
<i>tell Richard Matt
that they are ready to go</i>

33:51.195 --> 33:55.106
<i>so they can tell Mitchell
to be there the next night.</i>

33:55.191 --> 33:57.609
- And he says, "Matt, Matt,"
you know, "wake up."

33:57.693 --> 34:00.954
<i>And David takes
a single stogey that he has.</i>

34:01.113 --> 34:05.375
He has a mirror and he puts
his mirror outside of the cell

34:05.460 --> 34:08.036
<i>so that Matt on
the other side can see him.</i>

34:08.120 --> 34:10.213
<i>He can see his reflection.</i>

34:10.298 --> 34:12.123
<i>And Matt looks at David
and he goes,</i>

34:12.208 --> 34:14.217
<i>"Oh, man, you did it?</i>

34:14.376 --> 34:17.045
It's really here.
It's really happening."

34:17.129 --> 34:18.880
And David said,
"Yeah, we're ready.

34:18.964 --> 34:24.311
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:24.395 --> 34:27.898
<i>- Tonight will be the night.</i>

34:27.982 --> 34:31.818
<i>- From what Joyce tells me,
that day he looked at her</i>

34:31.903 --> 34:34.229
<i>and he raised his fist
in the air</i>

34:34.322 --> 34:37.148
<i>as if to say,
"We've done it."</i>

34:37.233 --> 34:40.318
And she knew in her heart
that this was the signal.

34:40.402 --> 34:43.655
<i>- Mitchell is to meet them
at midnight with her SUV.</i>

34:43.748 --> 34:47.826
<i>Meanwhile, David prepares
their getaway bags.</i>

34:47.919 --> 34:50.829
- Civilian clothing,
it's allowed by the state.

34:50.913 --> 34:54.999
So they could have a--like,
a red hoodie or sweatpants.

34:55.084 --> 34:57.928
- They had granola bars,
they had pepperoni,

34:58.012 --> 35:02.090
they had high-energy
and low-weight food items.

35:02.174 --> 35:05.936
<i>- The escape plan is all set.</i>

35:06.095 --> 35:09.347
<i>Now they just have to wait
for go time.</i>

35:09.431 --> 35:14.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:14.445 --> 35:16.446
<i>- Midnight staff will come
into the block,</i>

35:16.531 --> 35:21.693
they'll do their last
master count for the day,

35:21.786 --> 35:25.789
<i>and then shortly thereafter
it's lights out.</i>

35:25.873 --> 35:28.199
They went into action.

35:28.284 --> 35:30.293
<i>They put the mannequins
in their beds.</i>

35:30.452 --> 35:32.963
<i>They wrote their goodbye notes
in their cells.</i>

