36:40.114 --> 36:44.359
<i>He goes back down and he says,
"She's not here yet.</i>

36:44.443 --> 36:45.952
<i>Let's give her
a few more minutes maybe."</i>

36:46.037 --> 36:48.112
And Matt says,
"Yeah, oh, she'll be here."

36:48.206 --> 36:50.281
So they wait.

36:50.366 --> 36:56.454
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:56.538 --> 37:00.634
<i>And then at midnight, David
looks out of the hole again,</i>

37:00.793 --> 37:02.469
<i>No sign of Joyce.</i>

37:02.553 --> 37:04.387
<i>- So once inmates Matt and Sweat</i>

37:04.546 --> 37:07.548
<i>get out of the manhole,
the question is</i>

37:07.633 --> 37:09.634
where is Joyce?

37:09.727 --> 37:13.063
<i>- What David Sweat
and Richard Matt don't know</i>

37:13.222 --> 37:16.724
<i>is that Joyce Mitchell
has cold feet.</i>

37:16.809 --> 37:20.487
<i>In fact, she has checked
herself into the hospital</i>

37:20.571 --> 37:22.981
<i>for a panic attack.</i>

37:23.065 --> 37:24.899
<i>- Matt is baffled.</i>

37:24.984 --> 37:28.578
<i>He cannot believe
Joyce has not shown up.</i>

37:28.663 --> 37:32.165
And Matt says, "There's no way
I'm going back to my cell.

37:32.324 --> 37:35.743
<i>Let's get out of here."</i>

37:35.828 --> 37:39.414
<i>- Without a plan B
and without a getaway car,</i>

37:39.498 --> 37:42.175
<i>they head for
the surrounding mountains.</i>

37:42.260 --> 37:45.086
<i>Where they are headed
is unknown.</i>

37:45.170 --> 37:47.013
- There's no doubt in my mind
that they were headed

37:47.172 --> 37:49.173
to Joyce Mitchell's house.

37:49.258 --> 37:51.259
<i>Inmate Matt was quick
to tell the people</i>

37:51.352 --> 37:53.011
<i>you don't wanna ever rat me out</i>

37:53.095 --> 37:56.189
because I will not only get you
but I'll get your family,

37:56.348 --> 37:59.859
I'll get your dog, and I'll get
anything that you care about.

37:59.944 --> 38:03.530
And you will pay a hell of
a price for doing me wrong.

38:03.614 --> 38:06.366
There's no doubt in my mind
that inmate Matt

38:06.450 --> 38:10.445
had a score to settle
with Joyce Mitchell.

38:10.538 --> 38:13.448
<i>- They've escaped Dannemora.</i>

38:13.541 --> 38:16.376
<i>They have a five-hour
head start,</i>

38:16.460 --> 38:19.871
<i>and now they have
to escape a manhunt.</i>

38:19.955 --> 38:21.464
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:26.628 --> 38:28.388
<i>- Just before midnight
on June 5th, 2015,</i>

38:28.472 --> 38:30.798
<i>Richard Matt and David Sweat</i>

38:30.883 --> 38:33.551
<i>escaped Clinton
Correctional Facility</i>

38:33.635 --> 38:35.553
<i>in Dannemora, New York.</i>

38:35.637 --> 38:41.067
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:41.152 --> 38:42.319
- Inmates Matt and Sweat

38:42.403 --> 38:45.229
were found missing
at the standing headcount.

38:45.314 --> 38:48.816
- There's two holes
in the cells in A Block.

38:48.909 --> 38:50.994
<i>There are two inmates gone.</i>

38:51.078 --> 38:53.079
Holy [bleep].

38:53.164 --> 38:55.156
<i>And then when
they found the hole</i>

38:55.249 --> 38:57.408
<i>that went out through the pipe</i>

38:57.493 --> 38:59.085
<i>and then the manhole cover
that was moved,</i>

38:59.170 --> 39:02.005
<i>they knew those guys are gone.</i>

39:02.164 --> 39:03.840
Crazy.

39:03.999 --> 39:06.000
Crazy.

39:06.085 --> 39:08.753
<i>- I automatically became the
incident commander responsible</i>

39:08.846 --> 39:11.348
<i>for all operational
search efforts in the area.</i>

39:11.507 --> 39:14.601
They had quite a significant
six-hour head start.

39:14.760 --> 39:16.353
<i>Our plan was a massive</i>

39:16.437 --> 39:18.763
<i>immediate deployment
of personnel,</i>

39:18.856 --> 39:21.015
<i>hundreds of troopers
from around the state,</i>

39:21.108 --> 39:25.269
<i>mobile units
from multiple agencies.</i>

39:25.354 --> 39:27.447
<i>- Hundreds of police, forest
rangers and federal agents</i>

39:27.531 --> 39:28.615
<i>have been searching
for the pair.</i>

39:28.699 --> 39:30.200
- We're looking down
on the Adirondacks.

39:30.284 --> 39:34.204
That's 6 million acres
of trees and heavy woods.

39:34.363 --> 39:36.373
<i>- They're out there miserable.
They're hungry.</i>

39:36.532 --> 39:37.949
And desperate people
do desperate things.

39:38.033 --> 39:41.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:41.212 --> 39:43.454
<i>- The entire upstate region
of New York State</i>

39:43.547 --> 39:45.623
<i>is in a panic</i>

39:45.707 --> 39:48.292
<i>that two dangerous murderers
are on the loose.</i>

39:48.377 --> 39:49.961
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:50.045 --> 39:54.048
<i>As the authorities search for
David Sweat and Richard Matt,</i>

39:54.141 --> 39:55.967
<i>they are hiding out
in the woods,</i>

39:56.060 --> 39:59.470
<i>breaking into unoccupied
hunting cabins along the way.</i>

39:59.555 --> 40:02.473
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:02.558 --> 40:05.318
<i>At some point, David Sweat
and Richard Matt</i>

40:05.403 --> 40:07.487
<i>decide to split up.</i>

40:07.571 --> 40:10.231
- I think David and my dad split

40:10.324 --> 40:12.400
because my father found alcohol.

40:12.484 --> 40:15.236
<i>My dad definitely becomes
a different person</i>

40:15.320 --> 40:17.238
<i>when he's drinking
or under the influence.</i>

40:17.322 --> 40:20.667
<i>That is when one of his
more vicious personalities</i>

40:20.826 --> 40:23.161
<i>come out, absolutely.</i>

40:23.254 --> 40:24.495
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:24.580 --> 40:28.416
<i>- On June 26th, 21 days
since their escape,</i>

40:28.500 --> 40:31.010
<i>the authorities finally
catch up with Richard Matt</i>

40:31.170 --> 40:33.254
<i>near a hunting cabin.</i>

40:33.338 --> 40:36.266
- My father knew he was either
going to get captured

40:36.350 --> 40:37.675
or that they were
going to kill him.

40:37.768 --> 40:41.187
<i>He knew this was the end,
and he had a gun on him</i>

40:41.346 --> 40:42.522
<i>and he raised that gun</i>

40:42.606 --> 40:45.775
<i>and naturally the officers,
doing their job,</i>

40:45.860 --> 40:47.610
<i>they had to fire,</i>

40:47.769 --> 40:52.023
and come to find out
that gun was empty.

40:52.116 --> 40:55.610
<i>So my father knew that
if he raised a gun,</i>

40:55.694 --> 40:58.037
it was almost
choosing death by cop.

40:58.122 --> 41:01.199
<i>So it was almost his
invitation for them to shoot.</i>

41:01.283 --> 41:06.212
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:06.297 --> 41:08.214
<i>- Two days later, on June 28th,</i>

41:08.299 --> 41:10.041
<i>David Sweat is found</i>

41:10.125 --> 41:13.211
<i>by an officer
near the Canadian border.</i>

41:13.295 --> 41:14.545
<i>David refuses to stop</i>

41:14.630 --> 41:17.891
<i>when the officer yells
for him to surrender.</i>

41:17.975 --> 41:21.478
<i>- So he took careful aim
and squeezed off one round.</i>

41:21.637 --> 41:24.230
A bullet struck sweat
in the upper torso.

41:24.315 --> 41:28.234
<i>Sweat stumbled, but did
not fall and kept running.</i>

41:28.319 --> 41:30.737
Sergeant Cook
squeezed off another round.

41:30.896 --> 41:33.981
<i>The second round also hits
Sweat in the upper torso.</i>

41:34.066 --> 41:37.494
Backup was nearby and
immediately entered the field,

41:37.653 --> 41:40.071
applying first aid
and effectively saving

41:40.164 --> 41:43.908
David Sweat's life,
ending the 23-day manhunt.

41:44.001 --> 41:46.827
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:46.921 --> 41:49.923
- Through cunning,
coercion, ingenuity,

41:50.007 --> 41:54.093
and hours of tedious work,
Richard Matt and David sweat

41:54.178 --> 41:58.014
managed to do what no one
believed possible.

41:58.173 --> 42:03.019
They escaped the confines
of these walls,

42:03.103 --> 42:06.681
but the chain of events
that made their escape possible

42:06.774 --> 42:09.767
was only as strong
as its weakest link.

42:09.851 --> 42:12.520
<i>When Joyce Mitchell failed
to pick them up on the night</i>

42:12.604 --> 42:18.201
<i>of June 6th, 2015,
their fate was sealed.</i>

42:18.285 --> 42:20.537
<i>The 23-day manhunt that ensued</i>

42:20.696 --> 42:24.541
<i>cost New York State
over $23 million.</i>

42:24.625 --> 42:27.868
<i>Joyce pleaded guilty to
promoting prison contraband</i>

42:27.953 --> 42:29.963
<i>and criminal facilitation.</i>

42:30.122 --> 42:32.715
<i>She was fined $86,000</i>

42:32.800 --> 42:36.043
<i>and served more than
four years in prison.</i>

42:36.128 --> 42:38.296
<i>Corrections officer Gene Palmer</i>

42:38.389 --> 42:41.224
<i>pleaded guilty to
promoting prison contraband</i>

42:41.383 --> 42:43.801
<i>was sentenced
to six months in jail</i>

42:43.885 --> 42:47.471
<i>and fined $5,000.</i>

42:47.556 --> 42:50.650
<i>Richard Matt's determination
not to die in jail</i>

42:50.734 --> 42:52.977
cost him his life,

42:53.070 --> 42:55.229
and David Sweat,

42:55.314 --> 42:58.157
he's still serving
his life sentence,

42:58.317 --> 43:03.246
but now he's moved from prison
to prison every few years

43:03.330 --> 43:08.710
as they often find him
planning his next escape.
